NAS Homelab - Network Configuration Example

[ Local Network ]

Connection Type:
- Wired Ethernet (Fast Ethernet 100 Mbps)

IP Configuration:
- Static IP assigned via router DHCP reservation

Local Services:
- SSH
- SMB/CIFS
- OpenMediaVault Web UI

[ Remote Access ]

VPN Solution:
- Tailscale Mesh VPN (WireGuard-based)

Remote Access Methods:
- SSH via local IP
- SSH via Tailscale hostname
- OMV Web UI via internal VPN DNS

MagicDNS:
- Enabled for hostname-based access

Example Hostname:
- nas-homelab.tailnet.ts.net

[ Security ]

- No public port forwarding
- SSH access restricted through VPN
- Fail2Ban enabled
- SSH key authentication preferred

[ Operational Workflow ]

Primary Access:
- Desktop workstation on local LAN

Secondary Access:
- Smartphone via 5G + Tailscale
- Laptop remote administration

Management Tools:
- Termius (SSH/SFTP)
- OpenMediaVault Dashboard

[ Notes ]

- Tailscale remains active continuously
- NAS is not directly exposed to the public internet
- Performance limited by legacy 100 Mbps Ethernet hardware
- Remote management designed with simplicity and stability as priorities